"| \u2014\n|-\n! colspan=\"10\"| <small>\"\u2014\" denotes a release that did not chart.</small>\n|}\n\n===Music videos===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Song\n! Director\n! Ref.\n|-\n| 2010\n| \"Get What's Coming\"\n|\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web |title=Rival Sons - Get What's Coming [Official Video] |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fZvEHHekpKk |website=www.youtube.com |publisher=YouTube |accessdate=21 December 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2011\n| \"Pressure and Time\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Greg Ephraim\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web |title=Pressure And Time |url=https://imvdb.com/video/rival-sons/pressure-and-time |website=imvdb.com |publisher=IMVDB |accessdate=21 December 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| \"All Over The Road\"\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web |title=RIVAL SONS: 'All Over The Road' Video Released |url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/rival-sons-all-over-the-road-video-released/ |website=www.blabbermouth.net |publisher=Blabbermouth |accessdate=21 December 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2012\n| \"Face of Light\"\n| Dan Ruttley\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web |title=RIVAL SONS: 'Face Of Light' Video Released |url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/rival-sons-face-of-light-video-released/ |website=www.blabbermouth.net |publisher=Blabbermouth |accessdate=21 December 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| \"Keep On Swinging\"\n| Greg Ephraim\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web |title=RIVAL SONS Film 'Keep On Swinging' Video |url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/rival-sons-film-keep-on-swinging-video/ |website=www.blabbermouth.net |publisher=Blabbermouth |accessdate=21 December 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| \"Until the Sun Comes\"\n| Simon Gesrel\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web |title=Rival Sons - Until the Sun Comes |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_-oCues_BW4 |website=www.youtube.com |publisher=YouTube |accessdate=21 December 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2014\n| \"Open My Eyes\"\n| Greg Ephraim\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web |title=Open My Eyes (2014) |url=https://imvdb.com/video/rival-sons/open-my-eyes |website=imvdb.com |publisher=IMVDB |accessdate=21 December 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015\n| \"Electric Man\"\n| Markus Rutledge\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web |title=Electric Man (2015) |url=https://imvdb.com/video/rival-sons/electric-man |website=imvdb.com |publisher=IMVDB |accessdate=21 December 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2018\n| \"Do Your Worst\"\n| Andy Garza\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web |title=Rival Sons - Do Your Worst (Official Video) |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Vx60Fsu-w9M |website=www.youtube.com |publisher=YouTube |accessdate=21 December 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2019\n| \"Too Bad\"\n| Jordan Bellamy\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web |title=Rival Sons - Too Bad (Official Video) |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pBUHEMlqRiI |website=www.youtube.com |publisher=YouTube |accessdate=17 April 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| \"Sugar On The Bone\"\n| Patrik Skogl\u00f6w\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web |title=Rival Sons - Sugar On The Bone (Official Video) |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eSqkI8HmU84 |website=www.youtube.com |publisher=YouTube |accessdate=21 June 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|Year\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|Nominated work\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|Event\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|Award\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|Result\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"|2011\n|Rival Sons\n|rowspan=\"1\"|[[Classic Rock Roll of Honour Awards]]\n|Best New Band\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"|2012\n|Rival Sons\n|rowspan=\"1\"|[[Classic Rock Roll of Honour Awards]]\n|Breakthrough Artist\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"|2014\n|''Great Western Valkyrie''\n|rowspan=\"1\"|[[Classic Rock Roll of Honour Awards]]\n|Album of the Year\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2019\n|\"Too Bad\"\n|rowspan=\"1\"|[[Grammy Award]]\n|[[Grammy Award for Best Rock Performance]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|''Feral Roots''\n|rowspan=\"1\"|[[Grammy Award]]\n|[[Grammy Award for Best Rock Album]]\n|{{nom}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Rival Sons}}\n* [http://www.rivalsons.com/ Official website]\n\n{{Rival Sons}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:American blues rock musical groups]]\n[[Category:Earache Records artists]]\n[[Category:Hard rock musical groups from California]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2009]]\n[[Category:Musical groups from California]]\n[[Category:Musical quartets]]\n", "text_old": "{{excessive detail|date=October 2018}}\n{{Self-published|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Rival Sons\n| image           = Rival Sons Vienna.jpg\n| background      = group_or_band\n| origin          = [[Long Beach, California]], <br /> [[United States]]\n| genre           ={{flatlist|\n*[[Blues rock]]\n*[[hard rock]]\n*{{nowrap|[[rock and roll]]}}\n}}\n| years_active    = {{start date|2009}}\u2013present\n| label           = {{flatlist|\n*[[Earache Records|Earache]]\n*[[Warner Music Group]]\n*[[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n*[[Elektra Records|Elektra]]\n*[[Low Country Sound]] \n}}\n| website         = {{URL|rivalsons.com}}\n| current_members = \n* [[Jay Buchanan]]\n* [[Scott Holiday]]\n* [[Michael Miley]]\n* [[Dave Beste]]\n| past_members    = Robin Everhart\n| associated_acts = [[Dave Cobb]] <br/> [[Vance Powell]] <br/> [[Veruca Salt]] <br/>  [[Bloody Beetroots]] }}\n\n'''Rival Sons''' are an American [[Rock music|rock]] band formed in [[Long Beach, California]] in 2009. The group consists of lead vocalist [[Jay Buchanan]], guitarist [[Scott Holiday]], bassist Dave Beste and drummer Michael Miley. The band is also joined by touring keyboard player Todd \u00d6gren when on the road. They are signed to [[Atlantic Records]] via [[Dave Cobb]]'s label [[Low Country Sound]], an imprint of [[Elektra Records|Elektra]].\nThey have released six albums and one EP. \n\nThe band is known for their two Grammy nominations <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/artists/rival-sons}}</ref> , supporting [[Black Sabbath]] on [[The End Tour]], their extensive touring and their notable album release ''[[Pressure & Time]]''. .<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ventsmagazine.com/2018/02/27/rival-sons-sign-low-country-sound-atlantic-records-plot-new-album/|title=Rival Sons Sign Low Country Sound Atlantic Records Plot New Album|publisher=Allmusic|date= |accessdate=2014-05-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/therecord/2015/12/16/459972586/an-outsider-remakes-nashvilles-traditional-sound|title=An Outsider Remakes Nashville\u2019s Traditional Sound|publisher=NPR.org|date= |accessdate=2014-05-24}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n\n===Formation and debut album ''Before The Fire'' (2006\u20132009)===\nRival Sons formed in [[Long Beach, California|Long Beach]] where [[Jay Buchanan]] and Michael Miley lived. Prior to the formation of Rival Sons, [[Jay Buchanan]] recorded as a solo artist and with his ''Buchanan band''. He independently released ''All Understood'' in 2004 and ''True Love EP'' in 2006. Rival Sons formed from the remnants of guitarist [[Scott Holiday]]'s previous band.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/rival-sons-mn0002672136|title=Artist Rival Sons|publisher=Allmusic|date= |accessdate=2014-05-24}}</ref> He had previously been active in a number of bands including [[Human Lab]] who were signed to [[Atlantic Records]] which he then subsequently left and formed Black Summer Crush.\n\nIn 2006 Holiday came across Buchanan while searching on [[MySpace]] for a singer. Drummer Michael Miley had previously worked with Jay (as well as having been in [[Veruca Salt]] and the [[Carson Daly]] TV show band) and he had met bassist Robin Everhart playing at a benefit concert at [[Isaac Hayes]] house for [[Hurricane Katrina]] in [[Long Beach]]. The union of these four, Holiday, Buchanan, Everhart and Miley led to the formation of Rival Sons. \n\nAs a singer-songwriter [[Jay Buchanan]] was sceptical about joining a rock and roll band but after seeing the reception to the band's debut album ''Before the Fire'' (2009) produced by [[Dave Cobb]] Jay committed to Rival Sons full-time. Jack Rivera of the [[Huffington Post]] declared them \u201cA rock band to watch\u201d in November, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/jeff-rivera/rock-band-to-watch-rival_b_359148.html |title=Rock Band to Watch: Rival Sons &#124; Jeff Rivera |website=Huffingtonpost.com |date=2010-03-18 |accessdate=2016-01-20}}</ref> The band, following from this acclaim, were invited to perform as a supporting act for [[AC/DC]], [[Alice Cooper]], [[Black Sabbath]] and [[Kid Rock]] shows.<ref>[http://earache.tumblr.com/post/2166446667/new-signings-rival-sons-to-support-kid-rock-at New Signings]</ref> During this time, Rival Sons also performed on the race track during a televised show of [[Indianapolis 500|The Indianapolis 500]].<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://rockchoice.com/riaval-sons-to-rock-indy-500 |title=Rival Sons To Rock Indy 500 |publisher=Rock Choice |date=2010-08-10 |accessdate=2016-01-20}}</ref>\n\n=== EP, Signing and worldwide release of sophomore album ''Pressure & Time'' (2010\u20132011)===\n\nAfter the successful release of ''Before the Fire'', the band recorded a self-titled EP (independently released) in 2010, which caught the attention of [[Earache Records]] founder [[Digby Pearson]] and the band was subsequently offered a record deal in November, 2010. This signing immediately led to the band recording their notable album ''[[Pressure & Time]]'' on the Earache label in early 2011.\n\nTheir self-titled EP was re-released digitally by Earache Records in February, 2011, from which their debut European single, \u201cTorture\u201d was taken.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://earachenews.blogspot.co.uk/2011/01/rival-sons-self-titled-ep-out-now-on.html |title=Earache News: Rival Sons Self-Titled Ep Out Now On Itunes |website=Earachenews.blogspot.co.uk |date=2011-01-10 |accessdate=2016-01-20}}</ref>\n\nIn March, 2011 a string of shows at [[Canadian Music Week]], [[SXSW]] and the [[House of Blues]] were announced.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://earachenews.blogspot.co.uk/2011/03/rival-sons-announce-dates-at-canadian.html |title=Earache News: Rival Sons Announce Dates At Canadian Music Week, Sxsw And The House Of Blues |website=Earachenews.blogspot.co.uk |date=2011-03-04 |accessdate=2016-01-20}}</ref>\n\nRival Sons played at the [[Gene Simmons]]' \u201cAces & Angels\u201d [[Super Bowl]] party February 2, 2011<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://earachenews.blogspot.co.uk/2011/01/rival-sons-to-perform-at-super-bowl.html |title=Earache News: Rival Sons To Perform At Super Bowl Week Kick Off Event |website=Earachenews.blogspot.co.uk |date=2011-01-31 |accessdate=2016-01-20}}</ref> before making their European debut appearance at [[The Barfly|Camden Barfly]] on February 12, 2011 for the [[HMV]] Next Big Thing. The band [[Vintage Trouble]] supported their act and the show sold out in advance,<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://earachenews.blogspot.co.uk/2011/02/rival-sons-sell-out-debut-uk-show-in.html |title=Earache News: Rival Sons Sell Out Debut Uk Show In Advance |website=Earachenews.blogspot.co.uk |date=2011-02-11 |accessdate=2016-01-20}}</ref> which started a nearly unbroken string of European sell-out shows.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://earachenews.blogspot.co.uk/2011/11/rival-sons-arrive-in-europe-for.html |title=Earache News: Rival Sons Arrive In Europe For Headlining Tour |website=Earachenews.blogspot.co.uk |date=2011-11-03 |accessdate=2016-01-20}}</ref>\n\nRival Sons released their second LP album in June 2011 called ''[[Pressure & Time]]'', which reached number one on Amazon's Hard Rock best sellers and nineteen on the [[Billboard Hot 100]].<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/rock/7401032/rival-sons-new-album-hollow-bones-premiere|title=Rival Sons New Album Hollow Bones|website=Billboard|date=2016-06-09|accessdate=2016-01-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://earachenews.blogspot.co.uk/2011/04/rival-sons-reveal-pressure-time-album.html |title=Earache News: Rival Sons Reveal 'Pressure & Time' Album Cover |website=Earachenews.blogspot.co.uk |date=2011-04-21 |accessdate=2016-01-20}}</ref>\n\n[[Storm Thorgerson]] who had worked with bands such as [[Pink Floyd]], [[Led Zeppelin]] and [[Genesis (band)|Genesis]], created the cover art for the album voluntarily.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.creativebloq.com/graphic-design/10-classic-storm-thorgerson-album-cover-designs-4132447|title=Ten Classic Storm Thorgerson Album Cover Designs|publisher=Creative Bloq|date= |accessdate=2018-04-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.digitaljournal.com/a-and-e/music/interview-with-scott-holiday-from-rival-sons/article/387675|title=Interview with Scott Holiday from Rival Sons|publisher=Digital Journal|date= |accessdate=2018-04-07}}</ref> Storm liked Rival Sons, saying about the cover art;\n\n{{quote|\"I don't think you can be certain what's going on here. To me it's a picture about fear or concern. Here's someone about to descend and doesn't know what they'll face, or where this might lead. So, in his mind he's imagining the action. That's what you see, into his mind, as he focuses on what's about to happen.\n\nWhen he gets to the bottom of the stairs, where does he go? Turn left, right or straight ahead, anything's possible. And I hope this cover will have fans of the band intrigued for a long while. To me, the cover should be part of the album, and not just packaging.\u201d\n\n- Storm Thorgerson (2011)}}\n\nRival Sons played a string of Canadian dates in May 2011, as well as [[SXSW]], Hangout festival and [[The Viper Room]], before returning to Europe to play a series of European festivals such as [[Azkena Rock Festival|Azkena]], [[Sonisphere]], [[Rock Werchter]], [[Main Square Festival|Main Square]], Putte Parken, and [[Bospop]] in July 2011. Then the band joined [[Judas Priest]], [[Queensr\u00ffche]] and [[Lady Starlight]] on tour in the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.clashmusic.com/article/judas-priest-queensryche-rival-sons-live |title=Judas Priest / Queensryche / Rival Sons Live &#124; Features &#124; Clash Magazine |website=Clashmusic.com |date=2011-07-16 |accessdate=2016-01-20}}</ref>\n\nRival Sons' track \"Torture\" was featured in the film ''[[Real Steel]]'' in October 2011<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://earachenews.blogspot.co.uk/2011/10/rival-sons-track-featured-in-real-steel.html |title=Earache News: Rival Sons Track Featured In 'Real Steel' Movie |website=Earachenews.blogspot.co.uk |date=2011-10-13 |accessdate=2016-01-20}}</ref> and the band supported [[Evanescence]] by personal request of [[Amy Lee]] in the USA in October, 2011, who they would play with again in January, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://earachenews.blogspot.co.uk/2011/12/rival-sons-confirm-january-2012-us-tour.html |title=EARACHE NEWS: RIVAL SONS CONFIRM JANUARY 2012 U.S. TOUR WITH EVANESCENCE |website=Earachenews.blogspot.co.uk |date=2011-12-15 |accessdate=2016-01-20}}</ref>\nWhile Rival Sons continued to extensively tour, in 2012 they were featured on the [[Harald Schmidt Show]] as well as playing an acoustic set at the annual [[Classic Rock Roll of Honour Awards|Classic Rock awards]] located at the [[Roundhouse (venue)|Roundhouse]] in London. They were also voted \u2018Best New Band\u2019 by listeners of [[Planet Rock (radio station)|Planet Rock Radio]]. In mid 2012, ''Pressure & Time'' was voted number two album of the year and the band named \u201cBreakthrough Artist of the Year\u201d by [[Classic Rock Magazine]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.classicrockrevisited.com/show_interview.php?id=919|title=Rival Sons Interview|website=Classic Rock Revisited.com|date= |accessdate=2018-04-04}}</ref>\n\n===''Head Down'' and Dave Beste joins the band on bass (2012\u20132013)===\nIn February 2012 the band went into Honey Pye studios in [[Nashville, Tennessee]] for twenty days to record their third full-length LP album ''Head Down'' with [[Dave Cobb]] and this time award-winning engineer [[Vance Powell]] ([[Jack White]], [[The Raconteurs]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uaudio.com/blog/vance-powell-ua-interview/ |title=Vance Powell, GRAMMY\u00ae Winner for Best Engineered Album - Blog - Universal Audio |website=Uaudio.com |date= |accessdate=2016-01-20}}</ref>\n\nDuring this time, the album ''Pressure & Time'' was reissued as a deluxe edition from which the last single \u201cFace of Light\u201d was taken.  A video for the single was filmed in the UK\u2019s [[peak district]].<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://earachenews.blogspot.co.uk/2012/04/rival-sons-face-of-light-video.html |title=Earache News: Rival Sons: 'Face Of Light' Video Premieres On Vevo Front Page |website=Earachenews.blogspot.co.uk |date=2012-04-30 |accessdate=2016-01-20}}</ref> The band then embarked on US and [[Canadian]] shows including [[Rock on the Range]] and [[Big Music Fest]] before a string of European summer festivals including [[Rock Am Ring]], [[Sweden Rock]], [[Ruisrock]], Bukta, [[Graspop]] and [[Download Festival|Download]]. The band again also played European shows with Evanescence and [[Eagles of Death Metal]] as well as [[Black Stone Cherry]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://earachenews.blogspot.co.uk/2011/11/rival-sons-confirm-2012-uk-tour-with.html |title=EARACHE NEWS: RIVAL SONS CONFIRM 2012 UK TOUR WITH BLACK STONE CHERRY |website=Earachenews.blogspot.co.uk |date=2011-11-29 |accessdate=2016-01-20}}</ref>\n\nRival Sons third LP album ''[[Head Down (Rival Sons album)|Head Down]]'' was released in September, 2012 to critical acclaim.<ref>{{cite web|last=Walker |first=Lee |url=http://www.metalmouth.net/2012/08/rival-sons-head-down/ |title=RIVAL SONS \u2013 Head Down |publisher=MetalMouth |date=2012-08-22 |accessdate=2016-01-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/reviews/3v28 |title=Music - Review of Rival Sons - Head Down |publisher=BBC |date=2012-09-17 |accessdate=2016-01-20}}</ref> The album charted at number 31 in the UK album chart, number 5 in the UK indie chart, number 6 in Sweden, number 13 in Finland,  number 14 in Norway,  number 30 in Switzerland and number 38 in Germany. The debut single \u201cKeep On Swinging\u201d started a trend on Twitter, and the video was filmed in a church with snakes. The band then went on to complete another sold out European tour and were featured on the cover of [[Classic Rock (magazine)|Classic Rock Magazine]]. They also the \u2018Breakthrough artist\u2019 award presented by [[Vic Reeves]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stereoboard.com/content/view/176005/9 |title=Rival Sons Win Classic Rock \"Breakthrough Artist\" Award |publisher=Stereoboard |date=2012-11-14 |accessdate=2016-01-20}}</ref>\n\nIn January, 2013 the band released a second single from ''Head Down'' with a video for Until The Sun Comes directed by Simon Gesrel, known for his stop-motion work and his work with Michel Gondry ([[The White Stripes]], [[Bj\u00f6rk]]).<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://earachenews.blogspot.co.uk/2013/01/rival-sons-until-sun-comes-video.html |title=Earache News: Rival Sons \"Until The Sun Comes\" Video Premieres On Vevo |website=Earachenews.blogspot.co.uk |date=2013-01-03 |accessdate=2016-01-20}}</ref>\n\nIn March, 2013 the band recorded for ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' The Beat and appeared on ''[[Jimmy Kimmel Live]]''. On March 7, 2013 Rival Sons left on a tour of Europe supported by [[The Balconies]]. In April they toured the UK supported by The Graveltones and Ulysses culminating in a sold out show at [[Shepherds Bush Empire]]. Rival Sons also played a station session in [[St. Pancras, London]] for the second time to raise money for [[NSPCC]].\n\nRival Sons did a small mid-west USA tour in May before returning to Europe in June to play more summer festivals including Download, Kivenlahti Rock, [[Bergenfest]], [[Bravalla]], Main Square and [[Open Air St. Gallen]]. The band also supported [[Kiss (band)|Kiss]] in Italy and Switzerland. During this time bassist Robin Everhart quit the band for 'personal reasons' stating \"After years of intensive touring with Rival Sons, I have come to the conclusion that I am not a road-warrior and that the rock \u2019n\u2019 roll lifestyle\u2019 is not for me.\"<ref>http://www.msopr.com/press-releases/rival-sons-wish-the-best-to-departing-bassist-robin-everhart-dave-beste-will-fill-in-for-upcoming-u-s-tour-kicking-off-august-20/</ref>\n\nIn September 2013 Rival Sons supported [[Sammy Hagar]] across the US with new bassist Dave Beste, previously of [[Rocco DeLuca]] and the Burden. The band played Hard Rock Vegas in December and started the new year by headlining a street party in their hometown of [[Long Beach]].\n\n===''Great Western Valkyrie'', ''Hollow Bones'' and the [[Black Sabbath]] tour (2014\u20132017)===\n\nIn January, 2014 Rival Sons returned to the studio in Nashville with [[Dave Cobb]] to produce their fourth full-length LP album. Amidst great anticipation of their fan base, the critically acclaimed  ''[[Great Western Valkyrie]]'' was released in June, 2014. Even before the new album\u2019s release Rival Sons began their 2014 European Tour opening for [[Aerosmith]] in [[Helsinki, Finland]] and [[Stockholm, Sweden]]. The summer tour continued through Europe with club and festival dates in [[Germany]] at [[Rock Am Ring]] and [[Rock Im Park]], then onto four sold out shows in the United Kingdom and the legendary [[Isle of Wight Festival]].\n\nThey traveled back across the Atlantic to begin the USA 2014 summer tour with a sold out show at [[3rd and Lindsley]] in [[Nashville, TN]]. The US tour included several festivals and two sold out back to back dates in New York City. Rival Sons travelled back and forth between US and Canadian dates mid summer, before heading back to Northern Europe for four large festivals, ending the summer with a trip to [[South Africa]] to play the [[Oppikopi Festival]].\n\nAfter a rest Rival Sons began the second leg of the US tour playing dates in California including [[The Fillmore]] in San Francisco and a sold out show at the legendary [[The Troubadour, West Hollywood|The Troubadour]]. More Fall 2014 US Tour dates included shows in Arizona, Nebraska, Nevada, Massachusetts, Pennsylvania, New York, Maryland & New Jersey.\n\nRival Sons has had several live television performances in 2014, the first on [[Le Grand Journal (Canal+)]] then in October [[Late Night with David Letterman]] and [[Later\u2026 with Jools Holland]]. They performed live at the 2014 [[Classic Rock Magazine]] [[Classic Rock Roll of Honour Awards]]. In late 2014 Rival Sons fourth LP album ''[[Great Western Valkyrie]]'' was released. It was nominated for \u201cAlbum of the Year\u201d in 2014 by Classic Rock Magazine.\n\nIn October 2015 they recorded their fifth LP album ''[[Hollow Bones]]'', again with [[music producer]] Dave Cobb, in just three weeks. Rival Sons toured the United Kingdom from March to April, 2015 as well as played the main stage at Download Festival in 2016. Their LP album ''Hollow Bones'' was officially released July 2016.\n\nAfter the recording they toured with [[Deep Purple]] in their 2016 European tour. Throughout 2016 and into early 2017 they toured as main supporting act on the entirety of [[Black Sabbath]]\u2019s notable [[The End Tour]].<ref>{{cite magazine |title=Rival Sons |department=Tour advertisement |magazine=[[Kerrang!]] |publicationdate=17 January 2015 |issue= 1551 |page=27}}</ref>\n\n=== Signing to [[Atlantic Records]] and ''Feral Roots'' (2018\u20132019)===\n\nOn February 27, 2018 it was officially announced that Rival Sons had signed on with [[Low Country Sound]] an imprint of [[Elektra Records|Elektra]] run by Dave Cobb.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bravewords.com/news/rival-sons-sign-to-low-country-sound-atlantic-records-tour-dates-announced-around-shaky-knees-festival-performance |title=RIVAL SONS SIGN TO LOW COUNTRY SOUND / ATLANTIC RECORDS; TOUR DATES ANNOUNCED AROUND SHAKY KNEES FESTIVAL PERFORMANCE |publisher=Bravewords |date=2018-02-18 |accessdate=2018-02-18}}</ref>\n\nRival Sons released their sixth studio album ''[[Feral Roots]]'' on January 25, 2019,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/rival-sons-to-release-feral-roots-album-in-january/|title=RIVAL SONS To Release 'Feral Roots' Album In January|last=|first=|date=November 2, 2019|website=[[BLABBERMOUTH.NET]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=December 31, 2019}}</ref> to critical acclaim. The album received nominations for two awards at the [[2020 Grammy Awards]], one for [[Grammy Award for Best Rock Album|Best Rock Album]] and the other for [[Grammy Award for Best Rock Performance by a Duo or Group with Vocal|Best Rock Performance.]]\n\n==Artistry==\n\n===Songwriting and recording process===\n\nRival Sons early albums, including 'Pressure & Time', were written and recorded in the studio in an intense period of creativity. Speaking about the sophomore album that was written and recorded in 20 days, with producer [[Dave Cobb]], guitarist [[Scott Holiday]] states \"This is just the simplest way to not cheat ourselves or the listener, ROCK AND ROLL can't be over-thought, and if it is, it loses its immediacy and instinct...it needs to be a knife FIGHT, not a knife DANCE.\" <ref>https://www.planetrock.com/news/rock-news/rival-sons-reveal-new-album-details/title=Rival Sons Reveal New Album Details</ref>\n\nRival Sons have released seven records in ten years, recording regularly to deliver the immediacy needed for rock'n'roll. \"Opting to keep the sound intact and very accurate as to deliver to the listener exactly what was happening in the room when we put it down\" - [[Scott Holiday]] talking about the album ''Great Western Valkyrie''. <ref>https://loudwire.com/rival-sons-new-album-great-western-valkyre-june-release/</ref>\n<ref>https://www.musicradar.com/news/guitars/in-the-studio-rival-sons-638213</ref>\n\nThe band has a long standing, friendly and professional relationship with Grammy award winning music producer [[Dave Cobb]]. Cobb has worked on all of the band's album releases and is often referred to as another member of the band. He is interested in simplicity in the recording and with the sound and vitality of real musicians in a room. <ref>https://www.soundonsound.com/people/dave-cobb</ref> Dave encourages and captures the vocal punch of the band's mainman, Jay Buchanan. \"He's unbelievable, a one-take guy \u2014 done. It's such a pleasure, because then you can get wild with things. You can experiment when it doesn't take long for the singer to do his thing.\" <ref>https://www.soundonsound.com/people/dave-cobb</ref>\n\nRival Sons recording process changed for their major label debut ''Feral Roots'', for the first time writing and recording over a process of months. Jay Buchanan stated that \"You need to shift and constantly find new soil\" within the creative process, taking eight months to write and record the Grammy nominated album instead of all their previous work which took less than six weeks. <ref>https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/rival-sons-vocalist-says-bands-writing-process-is-just-like-farming-you-need-to-shift-and-constantly-find-new-soil/</ref>\n\n===Style and influences===\n\nRival Sons are often compared to sounds of the 1970's yet they cite [[Prince]], [[D\u2019Angelo]] and [[The Roots]] as influences alongside [[Muddy Waters]] and [[Howlin\u2019 Wolf]].<ref>https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/features/rival-sons-interview-how-the-blues-rockers-have-forged-their-own-path-to-fame-10123483.html</ref> Jay has listed artists from [[Joni Mitchell]] to [[Sly and the Family Stone]] amongst his influences, often stating [[Van Morrison]] as one of his heroes. \"I can\u2019t overstate his influence on me as a writer and vocalist\" - Louder Sound. <ref>https://www.loudersound.com/features/jay-buchanan-the-10-records-that-changed-my-life</ref>\n\u201cIt\u2019s a modern sound,\u201d insists Holiday, \u201cbecause it\u2019s being made right now\u201d.\n\nThe band are often cited for the sartorial style as well as their musical style, with Scott Holiday known for working with tailor ''Ray Brown'' and the band often wearing boots by UK bootmaker Jeffery West. Scott Holiday is known for his slim-line tailored suits, moustache and sunglasses, Jay Buchanan's style is unpredictable including wearing flowers in his hair,<ref>https://www.stereoboard.com/content/view/176005/9</ref> flowing floral shirts and tight leather suits. <ref>https://www.menstylefashion.com/rival-sons-reinvigorating-rocknrolls-roguish-charm/</ref>\n\n==Band members==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Current members===\n* [[Jay Buchanan]] \u2013 lead vocals, harmonica, rhythm guitar <small>(2009\u2013present)</small>\n* [[Scott Holiday]] \u2013 guitar, backing vocals <small>(2009\u2013present)</small>\n* Mike Miley \u2013 drums, backing vocals<small>(2009\u2013present)</small>\n* Dave Beste \u2013 bass, backing vocals <small>(2013\u2013present)</small>\n\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Former members===\n* Robin Everhart \u2013 bass <small>(2009\u20132013)</small>\n\n===Touring members===\n* Todd \u00d6gren \u2013 keyboards, percussion, backing vocals <small>(2014\u2013present)</small>\n{{col-end}}\n\n=== Timeline ===\n<!-- This is a timeline of the history of rock band Rival Sons -->\n<timeline>\nImageSize = width:800 height:auto barincrement:20\nPlotArea = left:90 bottom:80 top:0 right:5\nAlignbars = justify\nDateFormat = mm/dd/yyyy\nPeriod = from:01/01/2009 till:12/31/2019\nTimeAxis = orientation:horizontal format:yyyy\nLegend = orientation:horizontal position:bottom\nScaleMajor = increment:1 start:2009\nScaleMinor = increment:1 start:2009\